      "decision": "At-least-once delivery with idempotent handlers",
      "gains": "No message loss. Simple to reason about. Each service independently ensures idempotency via orderId+step deduplication.",
      "sacrifices": "Requires every handler to implement idempotency checks. Adds a deduplication table or check to each service.",
      "alternatives_considered": ["Exactly-once delivery: not achievable in distributed systems without significant complexity (Kafka transactions + careful consumer design). At-least-once + idempotency is the industry standard."]
